When someone asks you a direct question or when you see fit, you may respond out of turn order. In this case, Toric may respond to Sapphire prior to Gheant taking his turn, just so that the issue at hand is resolved. Do not post excessively and just ignore other players' turns, but do post out of order when there is a logical reason to. (someone asked you a question, a strong reaction to an event, a preemptive warning, shouting out the answer to a riddle, etc.).<br>
Hope this clears things up and makes the game go smoother.<br>
