Toric(tim)struggles to pull himself off of the ground.  He tries to stand but fails to raise his body up from the ice-cold stone. Soon he discovers himself too weak to lift himself AND his armor off of , so he does his best to unfasten his breastplate armor.  After much prying and pulling and grunting, he succeeds in loosening it enough so that he can crawl out.  The thing that stands out as he makes his way to his knees is his skin. And the burns that run all along his arms and back.  The human then attempts to kneel, but only succeeds in collapsing.  After more struggle and much physical strain, he manages to crawl back onto his hands and knees, at which point he raises his head and his tangled mane of fiery red hair. His face is slick with sweat and blood.  His slate-grey eyes are bulging with a mix of panic, relief, and emotional pain.  On the surface he appears calm and focused.  His eyes, however, tell a different story.  They belie an entirely different person buried within..They seem to have a dull glow to them, as if there's a torch burning hehind them. At first he can barely utter a sound.  But he soon struggles to whet his tongue and opens his mouth and begins to speak in response to the paladin's inquiry.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfaeryfirealongthenightshore.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gheantturtake@faeryfirealongthenightshore>Gheant Turtake</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The ultimate in Dwarven Defense.</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 6:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffaeryfirealongthenightshorefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: the horror...</span><hr size=1> Gheant seizes the box from Sapphire, squinting as he holds it up to torchlight to examine it. &quot;Hmm... this doesn't seem to be very valuable, but I value a good puzzle. What could this mean? Oh... and wee man, what are these things that you speak of?&quot; Gheant fondles the box as he waits for a reply... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfaeryfirealongthenightshore.showUserPublicProfile?gid=monkeysandhandgrenades>monkeysandhandgrenades</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Burning Cleric</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 6:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffaeryfirealongthenightshorefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re: horror....</span><hr size=1> &quot;Oh, I can assure you that that box you are holding is INDEED valuable.&quot;  The fire in Toric's eyes is burning brighter now.  &quot;More valuable that I think you realize.  That box is the reason I was pulled from battle.  I had been given explicit instructions to come directly here to guard the object I was to find here.  And that's it.  ..And even if that doesn't convince you.....these monks...GAVE THEIR LIVES... Suttox and his brethren valued whatever it is in this room enough to face utter destruction in order to save this.... So let me ASSURE you that this box is NOT a cheap toy.&quot;<br>
The unusually red-tinted human cleric struggles again to get out of his stricken position on the floor.  He decides that it's not worth it at this time, and is content with the cool stone.  He rolls onto his back so as to better address his interrogator.<br>
&quot; 'What are these things' you ask? I am not able to completely fulfill your question, but i do know that they appeared out of nowhere. Literally..OUT OF NOWHERE. One minute the monestary is a place of quiet contemplation, a place of safety, and...the next...its infested with beings the likes of which I have never seen.  I...they...it was horrible. Claws..and gaping mouths.  And..and burning red eyes.  But it wasn't the eyes that bothered me. It was the darkness behind them.  The empty void of darkness that lit their demonic faces.  I am certain that they are abominations...nothing like those...things..could be created through the power and the grace of Obad-Hai.......nothing....and they destroyed it. They destroyed all of them....I swear by the quarterstaff of Obad-Hai that I will find these monsters and exact due revenge....oh Suttox......&quot;<br>
The emotionaly drainedl human rolls back onto his stomach and exhales.  It's obvious that he is struggling to deal with so much death in such a short time.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfaeryfirealongthenightshore.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sovbeos>sovbeos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk Man Monster-killa</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 7:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffaeryfirealongthenightshorefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/sovbeos/stance.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Comfort</span><hr size=1> Serin quickly moves over to Toric to provide him some support, and a friendly hand he can touch.<br>
