~~the FIST OF FURY ~~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfaeryfirealongthenightshore.showUserPublicProfile?gid=monkeysandhandgrenades>monkeysandhandgrenades</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Burning Cleric</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 8:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffaeryfirealongthenightshorefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=51>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> open it if you'd like</span><hr size=1> As he takes the inviting hand of his new companion, Toric looks the monk square in the face.  Although initially intending to simply thank him for his compassion and understanding, the cleric finds himself staring deeply into the yellow eyes of his benefactor.  It's as if he's drawn there.  And with one quick glance, he realizes that he's found someone who could very well understand the turmoil burning inside of his heart.  Toric soon realizes what he is doing and quickly blinks his eyes so as to clear the fog that had settled through his long ordeal, and separates his gaze in order to focus on the question.  &quot;Any other information?? Yes, I think I might...although, I must say before I go on, that I was trapped in here from near the beginning, so my experience might not help you as much as you might like.  Anyway, you already know about the battle, and my task to guard this room.  Now let..me..seee...The battle had lasted only a few minutes..or maybe it was hours, i can't remember..when that invisible wall you found me locked behind appeared.  It don't know what its purpose was, but I think it might have been some sort of protective measure for the box, but I was unaware of this.  I was standing back there :<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> oints toward pedestal:: when it happened.  If it really was meant as protection, it was definitely triggered as a means of a last resort.  By that time, the battle would have been a lost cause.  However, the sound of combat still raged on, even with me trapped.  However, at some point, I began to hear a strangely eerie, soothing melody.  It seemed almost like a lament, or a farewell melody exchanged between lovers.  It was very enchanting.  Then I heard the grating of stone on stone in front of me.  Finally, there was a huge blast.  It shook the ground I stood on.  Then...silence.  Except that it wasn't silent, because i could hear a faint clicking...and a sound that reminded me of the clicking of my own breastplate armor as I am running.  Then there was nothing.  Nothing until you arrived.  Thank you once more.  You rescued me from a certainly long and painful death.  I am endebted to you.  All of you.  Now...about the box.  I have no grasp of what could possibly be contained, and what the monks were protecting, but I DO know that they went to a lot of trouble to protect it.  As far as actually opening it goes, I see no reason why you shouldn't let your own heart decide that.  I personally have no reason to look further.  Although it may contain some potent magic or even some clue as to why this place of solitude was disturbed by such evil forces.  No, I am through with the box.  I have protected it. And at the loss of my new friends.  These people who supported me in my time of chaos.  And now it's over. I've protected the box. My promise is fulfilled.&quot;<br>
With that, Toric takes the back of his hand to his forehead to wipe the sweat that has beaded there.  He then looks once more upon the monk. &quot;Thank you for the kind hand friend.&quot; And with a quick nod, Toric recognizes a kindred spirit to whom he owes his life. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfaeryfirealongthenightshore.showUserPublicProfile?gid=monkeysandhandgrenades>monkeysandhandgrenades</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Burning Cleric</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 9:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffaeryfirealongthenightshorefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> grrr...</span><hr size=1> OC: ok..that<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  is supposed to be a P...sorry...darned html.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfaeryfirealongthenightshore.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wintarroze@faeryfirealongthenightshore>WintarRoze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>rosey-posey pal</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(2/20/03 7:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffaeryfirealongthenightshorefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ho hum</span><hr size=1> &quot;Toric it seems as though you are weary. Have some fod ofours to reagian your strength. After that i done would you like to join our band and help us figure out this mystory?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><spa