Toric eyes the small chamber in which he has been kept prisoner for some time.  &quot;I do not believe that there is any way for us to continue in THIS:: points to back wall:: direction.  We should take back the path that led you here.&quot;  Toric strides out of the chamber, heading back towards the main chamber.  He appears to be in much higher spirits.  His eyes, upon a glance, are flames in and of themselves.  He appears able to burn right through the ground with his gaze....Something about him screams out &quot;man determined&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfaeryfirealongthenightshore.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gheantturtake@faeryfirealongthenightshore>Gheant Turtake</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The ultimate in Dwarven Defense.</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#333333>(2/25/03 8:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffaeryfirealongthenightshorefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Follow the leader</span><hr size=1> Gheant peers at the box as he shakes it back and forth, following Toric down the hallway. &quot;Ock, why won't ya open? If I had me a pint of me -secret- ale brew I bet ye'd be a little easier.&quot; Gheant face wrinkles in thought, and you can almost see the rusted gears in his head began to turn. &quot;This box ain't gonna get the best o' me!&quot; Gheant lifts the box to his face, taps the lid, and whispers: &quot;It's a SECRET that is too much for one, just enough for two, and nothing at all for three!.&quot;  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfaeryfirealongthenightshore.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gheantturtake@faeryfirealongthenightshore>Gheant Turtake</A> at: 2/25/03 8:07:05 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=l